cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MM

This paper deals with a priority queueing system in a communication network, which involves the transmission of packets generated randomly following Poisson processes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the computation of expected Peak Age of Information (PAoI), which is a metric related to information theory, indicating that cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category. The paper also considers different service disciplines, which are related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses the optimal ordering of priorities, which is related to optimization, making cs.PF (Performance) another possible category. Finally, the paper performs numerical studies, which are related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
